# .gitignore

```gitignore
## Ignore Visual Studio temporary files, build results, and
## files generated by popular Visual Studio add-ons.

# User-specific files
*.rsuser
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# Build results
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/

# Visual Studio cache/options directory
.vs/
	
# Rider
.idea/

# VS Code
.vscode/

# ASP.NET Scaffolding
ScaffoldingReadMe.txt

# Entity Framework
*.mdf
*.ldf

# Logs
*.log

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# NuGet
*.nupkg
packages/
!**/packages/build/

# Publish output
publish/
wwwroot/

# Environment variables
.env
appsettings.Development.json

# Test results
TestResults/
coverage/

# Generated files
Generated/

# SQL Server LocalDB
*.dbmdl

# Resharper
_ReSharper*/

# DotCover
*.dotCover

# Azure
.azure/

# Docker
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp
```

---

# README.md

````md
# Dotnet Learning

A personal learning repository for practicing and building backend APIs using ASP.NET Core Web API, Entity Framework Core, and SQL Server.

This project focuses on learning:

- ASP.NET Core Web API
- RESTful API design
- CRUD operations
- Entity Framework Core
- Repository Pattern
- DTOs (Data Transfer Objects)
- SQL Server integration
- Clean project structure
- Git and GitHub workflow

---

## Tech Stack

- ASP.NET Core Web API
- Entity Framework Core
- SQL Server
- C#
- Swagger / OpenAPI

---

## Features Implemented

### Regions Module

- Create Region
- Get All Regions
- Get Region By Id
- Update Region
- Delete Region

Implemented using:

- Domain Models
- DTOs
- Controllers
- Repository Pattern
- EF Core DbContext

---

## Project Structure

```text
MyProject.API/
│
├── Controllers/
├── Data/
├── DTOs/
├── Models/
│   ├── Domain/
│   └── DTO/
├── Repositories/
├── Migrations/
├── Program.cs
└── appsettings.json
````

---

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/dotnet-learning.git
```

### 2. Navigate to Project Folder

```bash
cd dotnet-learning
```

### 3. Restore Packages

```bash
dotnet restore
```

### 4. Update Database

```bash
dotnet ef database update
```

### 5. Run the Project

```bash
dotnet run
```

---

## API Testing

Swagger UI will be available at:

```text
https://localhost:<port>/swagger
```

---

## Learning Goals

This repository is being used to:

* Strengthen backend development skills
* Understand ASP.NET Core architecture
* Practice API development patterns
* Learn database integration using EF Core
* Improve GitHub project management

---

## Future Improvements

* Authentication & Authorization (JWT)
* Validation using FluentValidation
* AutoMapper integration
* Pagination & Filtering
* Logging
* Unit Testing
* Docker support
* Deployment

---

